</i></p><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-20_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Duty of Care in the health and social care environment refers to the obligation of care professionals to ensure the welfare of their clients by avoiding any actions that could cause harm and always acting in their client's best interests. It is a fundamental aspect of ethical healthcare. It forms a core part of the Care Certificate, a set of standards designed to equip health and social care workers with the knowledge and skills necessary to provide safe and compassionate care.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-dcc0" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dBFCZX khzvmY pf-22_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gvPcJq dRaLso"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-23_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-24_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-25_ pf-heading-1-h3">The importance of duty of care</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-27_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Understanding and implementing the duty of care is paramount. According to Skills for Care, this responsibility ensures that professionals not only meet the specific needs of their clients but also protect them from harm. This has significant implications for both care quality and legal compliance within care settings.



</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-29_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-30_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-31_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-33_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-34_ pf-text-1">Research indicates that effective training in Duty of Care significantly reduces incidents of negligence and malpractice in healthcare settings.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-36_ pf-text-1">The Care Quality Commission (CQC) reports that adherence to Duty of Care standards correlates with higher overall care quality ratings.
