</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-44_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-45_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Health and Social Care Act 2008</strong>&nbsp;- Establishes clear codes of practice for care providers.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-47_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Equality Act 2010</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Protects those receiving care from discrimination and ensures equal treatment under the provision of care services.








</li></ul><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-49_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">These laws, alongside guidelines from the Care Quality Commission (CQC), create a framework within which care must be delivered. Non-compliance can lead to legal repercussions and affect the safety and well-being of individuals in care.



